/root/tinkering/stop-git-std/docs/External-Board-Reviews/042026-v13-3-comparator-calibration/codex-r1-raw.log:2038:| 24 | [freerouting/freerouting](https://github.com/freerouting/freerouting) (wild scan) | `c5ad3c7` | 2026-04-20 | Critical | -- | **Ninth V1.2-schema wild scan — first Java V1.2 entry; first EDA (electronic-design-automation) category.** 1.7k-star Java PCB auto-router; 12-year solo andrasfuchs project (86.7% top-6 share — solo-maintainer flag FIRES). Used in KiCad workflows; loads Specctra DSN + serialized board snapshots. 7 findings: **F0 Critical — CONFIRMED Java deserialization RCE class**. `BasicBoard.java:108-110` invokes `ObjectInputStream.readObject()` on user-provided input streams; 35 source files import `java.io.ObjectInputStream`; Java serialization is core to the persistence model. Users opening a malicious serialized board file → gadget-chain RCE. Most-concrete RCE finding in the V1.2 catalog so far. F1 Warning solo-maintainer (andrasfuchs 86.7%) + anti-destruction-only ruleset (has `deletion` + `non_fast_forward` rules but NO review requirement); F2 Warning no SECURITY.md + 0 advisories in 12 years despite F0; F3 Warning 373-day release stall (v2.1.0 from 2025-04-12 while main pushed 2026-04-19); F4 **Info POSITIVE** Dependabot on Gradle actively producing dep-bump PRs (5 currently open); F5 Info 5 Gemini-AI workflows for triage/PR-review (different AI pattern from QuickLook's Copilot SWE agent); F6 Info Java/Gradle scanner ecosystem gaps. Community health 75% (CONTRIBUTING + CoC present — above catalog average). No split. **Q4 override** (`signal_vocabulary_gap`, 4th use of this label) — Phase 3 advisory amber (q4_has_critical_on_default_path=False by driver convention); Phase 4 red because F0's confirmed RCE class on user-loaded-files IS the default consumer path. Q1 red (genuine 86.7% solo) / Q2 green (active releases + Dependabot) / Q3 amber (CONTRIBUTING+CoC but no SECURITY.md) / Q4 red (override). All 4 gates clean. Commit `edf8f57`. | `methodology-used: continuous` | `v2.5-preview` (V1.2 schema) | [html](GitHub-Scanner-freerouting-v12.html) · [md](GitHub-Scanner-freerouting-v12.md) |
/root/tinkering/stop-git-std/docs/External-Board-Reviews/042026-v13-3-comparator-calibration/codex-r1-raw.log:2039:| 25 | [wled/WLED](https://github.com/wled/WLED) (wild scan) | `01328a6` | 2026-04-20 | Critical | -- | **Tenth V1.2-schema wild scan — first embedded-IoT-firmware entry in catalog** (ESP32/ESP8266 firmware for addressable LEDs over WiFi). 17.8k stars (largest in V1.2 catalog); 9-year project; transferred from Aircoookie to wled org 2025-01-31. Dispersed maintainer pattern (blazoncek 46.0% + Aircoookie 24.6% + 4 more contributors) — NOT solo. 100 total contributors. 68 releases; stable v0.15.4 (36d old), v16.0.0-beta (9d old), nightlies daily. 7 findings: **F0 Critical — unresolved private GHSA-2xwq-cxqw-wfv8** (issue #5340): researcher breakingsystems publicly complained 2026-02-02 about maintainer non-response after 10+ day private-advisory silence; maintainer softhack007 got HTTP 404 on own project's advisory (permissions misconfigured); netmindz last commented 2026-02-06 ('critical was fixed before; verifying 0.15.x backport') — **74 days silent, issue still open, 0.15.x backport publicly unconfirmed**. F1 Warning default-install has NO authentication (`correctPIN = !strlen(settingsPIN)` at wled_server.cpp:848) + CORS wildcard (line 342) + unauthenticated `/reset` (line 396) → any same-LAN page controls the device. F2 Warning supply-chain — `andelf/nightly-release@main` mutable ref in nightly.yml (PR #5386 proposes fix, 60 days unmerged); 0 SHA-pinned actions across 8 workflows; `pull_request_target` in pr-merge.yaml. F3 Warning anti-destruction-only ruleset (`deletion` + `non_fast_forward` only) + no CODEOWNERS **despite 38% formal / 86% any-review (second-highest / highest in V1.2 catalog respectively)** — strong social review without structural enforcement. F4 Warning no SECURITY.md in 9 years + documented private-advisory permissions gap. F5 Info build-time Python deps carry 73 CVEs (urllib3×28, requests×13, starlette×7, bottle×8, etc.) via platformio — firmware ships pure C++, so BUILD-TIME only. F6 Info scanner coverage gaps (ArduinoJson deserializeJson regex false-positives × 19, ghostly npm-wled channel, q2 security-keyword FP on PR #4942 feature title). No split — factory-default install is dominant consumer experience. **Q4 override** (`signal_vocabulary_gap`, 5th use of this label) — compute has no harness-derivable signal for firmware-default-no-auth + LAN-trust-model; Phase 4 authored q4_has_critical_on_default_path=True based on F0 + F1. Q1 red / Q2 red / Q3 amber / Q4 red (override). 11/11 V1.2 wild scans with 0 published GHSA advisories — silent-fix pattern catalog-wide. Active CodeQL + Copilot SWE agent + Copilot review workflows (above-average CI posture). All 4 gates clean. Commit `b3622b5`. | `methodology-used: continuous` | `v2.5-preview` (V1.2 schema) | [html](GitHub-Scanner-WLED.html) · [md](GitHub-Scanner-WLED.md) |
/root/tinkering/stop-git-std/docs/board-review-data/scan-bundles/Kronos-67b630e.json:1593:        "summary": "All four scorecard cells land at red. Q1 and Q3 align with the Phase 3 advisory and need no override. Q2 and Q4 are ESCALATE overrides: Phase 3 compute returned amber on both because its signals are sparse (open_security_issue_count=1 alone is thin for Q2; q4_has_critical_on_default_path=False missed the pickle path entirely). Phase 4 sees the qualitative context \u2014 disclosed 95-day RCE, 48-CVE dep graph, no-release install model \u2014 and escalates Q2 to red (override_reason=signal_vocabulary_gap \u2014 the compute signal's domain doesn't include open issues) and Q4 to red (override_reason=harness_coverage_gap \u2014 the dangerous_primitives regex missed the pickle.load in finetune/dataset.py:42)."
/root/tinkering/stop-git-std/docs/board-review-data/scan-bundles/Kronos-67b630e.json:2171:        "rationale": "The Phase 3 advisory computed amber because compute.py's Q4 signals report `q4_has_critical_on_default_path=False` and `q4_has_warning_on_install_path=False` (both derived from harness coverage that did not confirm a critical on the install path \u2014 the dangerous_primitives deserialization family missed the pickle.load at finetune/dataset.py:42; see E12 coverage gap). Phase 4 sees (1) an unambiguous disclosed RCE on the documented finetune path (F0); (2) the only install model is `pip install -r requirements.txt` from a master checkout with no release boundary (F3); (3) the dependency graph ships 48 known CVEs (F1) with loose/unpinned requirements; (4) no artifact verification of any kind \u2014 no SLSA, no signed wheels, no checksums. 'Out of the box safe' is not a defensible reading for a finetune user. Red reflects the realistic consumer experience on the documented default path.",
/root/tinkering/stop-git-std/docs/External-Board-Reviews/042026-v13-3-comparator-calibration/r3-brief.md:77:**Context:** V3Q2 asked whether to land Priority 1 (compute derivation: `q4_has_critical_on_default_path = True` when `dangerous_primitives.deserialization.hit_count ≥ N` AND tool loads user files) in V1.2.x. Skeptic repeated DISAGREE at R2 with a stronger framing: "the deserialization primitive family is conceptually broken — fix requires primitive taxonomy redesign, not a language qualifier."
/root/tinkering/stop-git-std/docs/External-Board-Reviews/042026-v13-3-comparator-calibration/r3-brief.md:106:**Context:** V3Q4 asked whether to land Priority 1c (compute derivation: README disclaimer phrase match + `reverse-engineering` topic + platform-name match → `q4_has_critical_on_default_path = True`). Skeptic has held D3 (REJECT permanently) across both rounds.
/root/tinkering/stop-git-std/docs/board-review-data/scan-bundles/freerouting-c5ad3c7.json:3439:        "summary": "One scorecard override on Q4: Phase 3 advisory computed amber via the standard rubric (q4_has_critical_on_default_path=False by driver convention \u2014 the signal is expected to be set by Phase 4 authoring). Phase 4 authored F0 Critical (Java ObjectInputStream RCE class on the documented consumer file-loading path), which makes the default-path-critical condition true in judgment. override_reason = signal_vocabulary_gap \u2014 the compute signal vocabulary doesn't directly read from dangerous_primitives.deserialization.hit_count; a widening that auto-fires q4_has_critical_on_default_path when deserialization hits >= N on a file-loading tool would close the override loop. Q1 red genuine (solo-maintainer 86.7% + 9.5% formal review), Q2 green (active Dependabot + main), Q3 amber (CONTRIBUTING + CoC present, SECURITY.md absent)."
/root/tinkering/stop-git-std/docs/board-review-data/scan-bundles/freerouting-c5ad3c7.json:3975:        "rationale": "The Phase 3 advisory computed amber via compute.py's Q4 rubric (q4_has_critical_on_default_path=False, since that signal is hardcoded False in the build_form driver pending Phase 4 authoring). Phase 4 has now authored F0 \u2014 a Critical severity finding confirming `ObjectInputStream.readObject()` is invoked on user-provided input streams (BasicBoard.java:108-110, E1), with 35 files importing ObjectInputStream (E2) indicating Java serialization is core to the data-persistence model. freerouting's primary documented workflow is users opening PCB design files, including serialized board state \u2014 the same paths that flow into the deserialization surface. This makes has_critical_on_default_path=True in the judgment-sense, even though the compute signal input is False by driver convention. The `q4_has_critical_on_default_path` signal conceptually exists but its input pathway doesn't read dangerous_primitives.deserialization.hit_count \u2014 it relies on Phase 4 setting the bool. This is a signal-vocabulary calibration issue, not a harness coverage issue (the harness correctly detected 35 deserialization hits).",
/root/tinkering/stop-git-std/docs/board-review-data/scan-bundles/freerouting-c5ad3c7.json:3977:        "suggested_threshold_adjustment": "Add a compute-side derivation: if dangerous_primitives.deserialization.hit_count >= N (e.g., 5) AND the tool is documented as loading user files (README pattern match for 'open file' / 'import' / 'load'), auto-set q4_has_critical_on_default_path=True. This would close the override loop for the Java/Python/similar-serialization-prone-languages case.",
/root/tinkering/stop-git-std/docs/SCANNER-OPERATOR-GUIDE.md:559:- **D-7 Scorecard cell authority migration (V1.1 → V1.2) — COMMITTED, not conditional.** Added by SF1 board review 2026-04-20 (`docs/External-Board-Reviews/042026-sf1-calibration/CONSOLIDATION.md`). Move scorecard cell colors out of `phase_3_computed.scorecard_cells` into `phase_4_structured_llm.scorecard_cells` with structured-constraint fields: `question`, `color` (red|amber|green enum), `short_answer`, `rationale` (must cite E-IDs), `edge_case` (bool), `suggested_threshold_adjustment` (optional — feedback loop), `computed_signal_refs` (list). Demote `compute_scorecard_cells()` to advisory — output surfaces as `phase_3_advisory.scorecard_hints` for Phase 4 LLM to consult. Gate 6.3 changes from "cell-by-cell match" to "cells present + rationale cites evidence + LLM override of advisory hint explained with `edge_case=true`." Step 3b byte-for-byte requirement RETAINED for the other 7 Phase 3 operations.
