/root/tinkering/stop-git-std/docs/board-review-data/scan-bundles/Baileys-8e5093c.json:3118:        "summary": "One scorecard override on Q4: Phase 3 advisory computed amber via the standard Q4 rubric (q4_has_critical_on_default_path=False by driver convention). Phase 4 authored F0 Critical \u2014 the reverse-engineered-API-library shape produces a default-path critical that isn't surfaced by any harness-derived signal. override_reason = signal_vocabulary_gap (5th Q4 use of this label in V1.2 catalog, 6th overall). Q1 red genuine (0 governance + 89.5% top-2 concentration), Q2 red genuine (PR #1996 stale-out + 14 runtime CVEs + 150-day stall), Q3 red genuine (no SECURITY.md + 0 advisories + documented disclosure-handling failure). This is the first V1.2 wild scan with all 4 cells RED \u2014 prior high-severity scans had at least one amber (typically Q3) softening the pattern."
